T*
(## 1.3 How AR Systems Work) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(AR must solve two core problems: **tracking** \(where am I in the world?\) and **rendering** \(how) Tj
T*
(do I blend virtual and real visually?\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1.3.1 AR Tracking Methods) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Marker-Based AR:**  ) Tj
T*
(- Fiducial markers \(ArUco, QR codes, Vuforia targets\) are recognized by computer vision) Tj
T*
(- The known marker geometry allows computing camera pose via PnP \(Perspective-n-Point\)) Tj
T*
(algorithm) Tj
T*
(- Simple, fast, but requires a physical marker) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Markerless AR \(SLAM-based\):**  ) Tj
T*
(- SLAM = Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) Tj
T*
(- The device builds a map of the environment while simultaneously localizing itself within it) Tj
T*
(- Feature points \(SIFT, ORB, FAST\) are extracted from camera frames; matched frame-to-frame) Tj
T*
(- **ARKit** \(Apple\) and **ARCore** \(Google\) implement SLAM + Visual-Inertial Odometry \(VIO\) on) Tj
T*
(phones) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Plane Detection:**  ) Tj
T*
(ARKit/ARCore detect horizontal and vertical planes using depth sensors or monocular depth) Tj
T*
(estimation, enabling virtual objects to sit on surfaces.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**LiDAR-based depth scanning \(iPhone 12 Pro+, iPad Pro\):**  ) Tj
T*
(Direct depth measurement allows instant surface reconstruction, occlusion handling, and faster) Tj
T*
(SLAM initialization.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1.3.2 Registration and Rendering in AR) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Registration** = aligning virtual content with the real world with pixel-level accuracy.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key challenges:) Tj
T*
(- **Dynamic lighting:** The virtual object must be lit to match the real environment \(Spherical) Tj
T*
