(# Chapter 2 ? Geometric Modeling {#chapter-2}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Geometric modeling is the mathematical description and manipulation of 3D shapes. After) Tj
T*
(acquiring 3D data \(from LiDAR, photogrammetry, CT/MRI, etc.\), we must process the raw data into) Tj
T*
(clean, useful representations.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2.1 Point Clouds) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.1.1 What is a Point Cloud?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A **point cloud** is an unordered set of 3D points P = {p?, p?, ..., p?} where each point p? =) Tj
T*
(\(x?, y?, z?\) represents a position in 3D space. Points may also carry additional attributes:) Tj
T*
(color \(R,G,B\), surface normals, intensity \(from LiDAR\), or timestamps.) Tj
T*
