() Tj
T*
(**Acquisition methods:**) Tj
T*
(- **LiDAR \(Light Detection and Ranging\):** A laser pulse is fired and the time-of-flight) Tj
T*
(measured. Used in autonomous vehicles, surveying, and industrial scanning.) Tj
T*
(- **Structured Light Scanners:** Project a known light pattern \(e.g., sinusoidal stripes\);) Tj
T*
(deformation of the pattern encodes depth \(Intel RealSense D-series, Kinect\)) Tj
T*
(- **Time-of-Flight Cameras:** Each pixel measures round-trip photon travel time \(iToF, dToF\)) Tj
T*
(- **Photogrammetry:** Multiple overlapping images are processed by Structure from Motion \(SfM\)) Tj
T*
(algorithms to produce a dense point cloud) Tj
T*
(- **CT/MRI:** Medical scans provide 3D volumetric data that can be thresholded into point) Tj
T*
(clouds) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.1.2 Point Cloud Data Structures) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Efficient processing requires spatial data structures:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**k-d Tree:**  ) Tj
T*
(A binary space-partitioning tree. Splits space alternately along x, y, z axes at median points.) Tj
T*
(Supports O\(log n\) nearest-neighbor queries. Used extensively in ICP, normal estimation, and) Tj
T*
(radius searches.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Build: choose axis with max variance ? find median ? recurse on left/right) Tj
T*
(Query: traverse tree, prune branches where minimum possible distance > current best) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Octree:**  ) Tj
T*
(Recursively divides 3D space into 8 equal octants. Good for uniform density clouds; used for) Tj
T*
(compression and level-of-detail.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Voxel Grid:**  ) Tj
T*
(Divides space into equal cubes \(voxels\). Points in each voxel are replaced by their centroid ?) Tj
T*
(a common downsampling strategy.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.1.3 Normal Estimation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Normals are needed for rendering and surface reconstruction. For each point p?:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Find k-nearest neighbors \(k typically 10?30\)) Tj
T*
(2. Compute the covariance matrix C of the neighbor coordinates) Tj
T*
(3. Perform PCA \(eigendecomposition\) on C) Tj
T*
(4. The normal is the eigenvector corresponding to the smallest eigenvalue \(the direction of) Tj
T*
(least variance\)) Tj
T*
(5. Orient normals consistently \(e.g., using minimum spanning tree or camera viewpoint\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2.2 Triangulation ? Turning Points into Meshes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.2.1 Why Triangulate?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A point cloud has no topology ? we don't know which points are neighbors on the surface.) Tj
T*
(Triangulation creates a **triangle mesh** \(also called a **polygonal mesh** or **TIN ?) Tj
T*
(Triangulated Irregular Network**\), which gives us:) Tj
T*
(- Continuous surface for rendering) Tj
T*
(- Well-defined surface normals per face) Tj
T*
(- Topology for further geometric processing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.2.2 Delaunay Triangulation \(2D\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Definition:** Given a set of points P in the plane, the Delaunay triangulation DT\(P\) is the) Tj
T*
(unique triangulation such that **no point in P lies inside the circumcircle of any triangle**) Tj
T*
(in DT\(P\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Properties:**) Tj
T*
(- Maximizes the minimum angle among all triangles ? avoids thin, degenerate "sliver" triangles) Tj
T*
ET
