(## 2.3 Mesh Simplification) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.3.1 Why Simplify?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Raw scans can contain millions of triangles. Simplification reduces the triangle count while) Tj
T*
(preserving visual quality. This is essential for:) Tj
T*
(- Real-time rendering \(games, VR\)) Tj
T*
(- Level of Detail \(LOD\) systems) Tj
T*
(- Transmission over networks) Tj
T*
(- Faster downstream processing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.3.2 Quadric Error Metrics \(QEM\) ? Garland & Heckbert \(1997\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The most widely used mesh simplification algorithm.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Core Idea:** For each vertex, maintain a 44 symmetric matrix Q \(the "quadric"\) that measures) Tj
T*
(the squared distance from the vertex to the set of planes of its adjacent triangles. Collapsing) Tj
T*
(an edge merges two vertices; the error of the collapse is the quadric error at the merged) Tj
T*
(position.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Algorithm:**) Tj
T*
(1. Compute Q matrix for every vertex \(sum of outer products of plane equations of adjacent) Tj
T*
(faces\)) Tj
T*
(2. For each edge \(v?, v?\), compute optimal contracted position v? = argmin\(v?? Q_total v?\) and) Tj
T*
(its error) Tj
T*
(3. Insert all edges into a min-heap ordered by error) Tj
T*
(4. Repeatedly extract the minimum-error edge and collapse it) Tj
T*
(5. Update Q matrices and edge costs for neighbors) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Error metric:**  ) Tj
T*
(For a plane defined by ax + by + cz + d = 0 \(with a + b + c = 1\), the squared distance from) Tj
T*
(point **p** = [x,y,z,1]? is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(error\(p\) = p? K p) Tj
T*
(where K = pp? \(outer product of the plane vector p = [a,b,c,d]\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The vertex quadric Q = ? K over all adjacent planes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Results:** Can reduce a 100,000 triangle mesh to 1,000 triangles with < 1% visual degradation) Tj
T*
(if done carefully.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.3.3 Other Simplification Methods) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Vertex Clustering:** Divide space into a grid; replace all vertices in each cell by a single) Tj
T*
(representative. Fast but can create artifacts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Progressive Meshes \(Hoppe, 1996\):** Record each edge collapse as a reversible operation;) Tj
T*
(store the original mesh as a sequence of "vertex splits." At runtime, apply the desired number) Tj
T*
(of splits for adaptive LOD.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**View-Dependent Simplification:** Keep fine detail in regions close to the camera; use fewer) Tj
T*
(triangles far away. Dynamically updates as the viewpoint changes.) Tj
T*
