54 738 Td
(### 2.5.1 Sources of Noise) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Scanner hardware limitations \(quantization noise, sensor noise\)) Tj
T*
(- Multi-path reflections \(LiDAR bounces off multiple surfaces\)) Tj
T*
(- Dust, humidity, vibration during scanning) Tj
T*
(- Registration errors when combining multiple scans) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Noise manifests as:) Tj
T*
(- **Outliers:** Points far from the true surface \(gross errors\)) Tj
T*
(- **High-frequency noise:** Points near the surface but randomly scattered around it) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.2 Statistical Outlier Removal \(SOR\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For each point p?:) Tj
T*
(1. Find k nearest neighbors) Tj
T*
(2. Compute mean distance ?? and standard deviation ?? of distances to neighbors) Tj
T*
(3. Compute global mean ? and standard deviation ? across all points) Tj
T*
(4. Remove point if ?? > ? + ?? \(where ? is a threshold, typically 1.0?2.0\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This removes isolated points that are far from their neighborhood.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.3 Radius Outlier Removal) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Remove points that have fewer than N neighbors within a radius r. Very fast; removes isolated) Tj
T*
(points in sparse regions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.4 Bilateral Filtering for Point Clouds) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Adapted from image processing. For each point p?, compute a new position p'? as a weighted) Tj
T*
(average of neighbors:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(p'? = ?? w\(p?, p?\)  p?  /  ?? w\(p?, p?\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(w\(p?, p?\) = exp\(?||p??p?|| / ?_spatial\)  exp\(?||n?\(p??p?\)|| / ?_normal\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The first term uses spatial proximity; the second uses projected distance along the normal) Tj
T*
(direction \(preserving edges and sharp features\). ? values control the smoothing strength.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.5 Moving Least Squares \(MLS\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The MLS method fits a local polynomial surface to the neighborhood of each point and projects) Tj
T*
(the point onto that surface:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. For each point p?, gather k-nearest neighbors) Tj
T*
(2. Fit a local plane or low-degree polynomial p\(u,v\) to those neighbors by least-squares, with) Tj
T*
(Gaussian weights centered at p?) Tj
T*
(3. Project p? onto the fitted surface) Tj
T*
(4. Recompute normals from the surface fit) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MLS both smooths and regularizes ? moving noisy points onto a smooth implicit surface. It is) Tj
T*
(the basis of the **APSS \(Algebraic Point Set Surfaces\)** method.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.6 Voxel Downsampling \(Regularization\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(To make a point set "more regular" \(uniform density\):) Tj
T*
(1. Create a 3D voxel grid of cell size `leaf_size`) Tj
T*
(2. All points in each voxel cell are replaced by their centroid) Tj
T*
(3. Result: one point per non-empty voxel ? uniform density) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Fast O\(n log n\) implementation in PCL \(Point Cloud Library\) and Open3D.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.5.7 Comparison of Denoising Methods) Tj
T*
