T*
(## 3.1 CT Scanning \(Computed Tomography\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.1.1 Physical Principle) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CT uses **X-rays** ? ionizing electromagnetic radiation. A rotating X-ray source and detector) Tj
T*
(array around the patient take hundreds of 2D projection images \(sinograms\) from different) Tj
T*
(angles. A mathematical procedure called **back-projection** \(specifically **filtered) Tj
T*
(back-projection**, FBP\) reconstructs the 3D density distribution.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Hounsfield Units \(HU\):**  ) Tj
T*
(The attenuation of X-rays by tissue is expressed in Hounsfield Units:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Tissue | HU Value |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Air | ?1000 |) Tj
T*
(| Lung | ?500 to ?700 |) Tj
T*
(| Fat | ?100 to ?50 |) Tj
T*
(| Water | 0 |) Tj
T*
(| Soft tissue | +20 to +80 |) Tj
T*
(| Bone | +300 to +1900 |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This allows **windowing** ? adjusting contrast and brightness to highlight specific tissue) Tj
T*
(types.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.1.2 CT Reconstruction Algorithm ? Filtered Back-Projection) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. **Projection acquisition:** For each angle ?, measure the line integral of X-ray attenuation) Tj
T*
(along every ray through the object ? produces the **Radon transform** R?\(s\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. **Filtering step:** Apply a ramp filter \(Ram-Lak filter\) in the frequency domain to each) Tj
T*
(projection:  ) Tj
T*
(   `H\(f\) = |f|` \(enhances high frequencies, counteracts blurring from back-projection\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. **Back-projection:** For each filtered projection, smear the values back along the ray paths) Tj
T*
(and sum up:  ) Tj
T*
(   `f\(x,y\) = ??^? P_?\(x cos? + y sin?\) d?`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. **Result:** A 3D voxel grid showing tissue density.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Iterative reconstruction \(IR\):** Modern CT scanners use iterative methods \(ASIR, IRIS,) Tj
T*
(SAFIRE\) that model noise statistics and scanner physics, allowing lower radiation doses with) Tj
T*
(comparable image quality.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.1.3 CT Advantages and Disadvantages) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Advantages:**) Tj
T*
(- Excellent for bone, calcifications, lung) Tj
T*
(- Fast acquisition \(entire chest in one breath-hold\)) Tj
T*
(- Wide availability) Tj
T*
(- Precise HU values enable automated segmentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
