(### 3.3.1 Workflow Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(CT/MRI Acquisition) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(DICOM Data \(stack of 2D slices, e.g., 512512  300 slices\)) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(Segmentation \(which voxels belong to the target structure?\)) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(3D Surface Extraction \(Marching Cubes\)) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(Mesh Post-Processing \(smoothing, hole filling, simplification\)) Tj
T*
(        ?) Tj
T*
(Visualization / 3D Printing / Surgical Planning) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.3.2 Segmentation Methods) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Thresholding:**  ) Tj
T*
(For bone: any voxel with HU > 300 is classified as bone. Fast and effective for high-contrast) Tj
T*
(structures \(CT bone, lung\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Region Growing:**  ) Tj
T*
(1. Place a seed point inside the target organ) Tj
T*
(2. Recursively add adjacent voxels if their intensity is within a tolerance range) Tj
T*
(3. Stops at edges \(abrupt intensity changes\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Watershed Segmentation:**  ) Tj
T*
(Treat the image as a topographic map; flood from local minima; watershed lines separate) Tj
T*
(different regions. Good for touching structures.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Active Contours \(Snakes, Level Sets\):**  ) Tj
T*
(Evolve a curve/surface toward object boundaries by minimizing an energy:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(E = E_internal \(smoothness\) + E_external \(image gradient\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Level set methods represent the surface implicitly as the zero-level of a function ?\(x,y,z\),) Tj
T*
(which evolves according to:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(??/?t = |??| \(? + F\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(where ? is curvature and F is the image-based speed term.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Deep Learning Segmentation:**  ) Tj
T*
(- **U-Net \(Ronneberger et al., 2015\):** The dominant architecture for medical image) Tj
T*
(segmentation) Tj
T*
(  - Encoder path: consecutive conv + max-pool \(extracts features, increases receptive field\)) Tj
T*
(  - Bottleneck: lowest resolution) Tj
T*
(  - Decoder path: upsampling + skip connections from encoder \(restores spatial detail\)) Tj
T*
(  - Output: pixel-wise probability map) Tj
T*
(- **3D U-Net:** Extends to volumetric segmentation) Tj
T*
(- **nnU-Net:** Self-configuring framework that adapts to any segmentation dataset automatically) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.3.3 Marching Cubes Applied to Medical Data) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(After segmentation, the binary volume is passed to Marching Cubes:) Tj
T*
(1. Each 222 voxel cube has 8 corners classified as inside/outside the object) Tj
T*
(2. 256 configurations ? 15 unique cases by symmetry) Tj
T*
(3. Each case defines which edges are intersected and how to place triangles) Tj
T*
(4. Linear interpolation finds precise edge intersection positions) Tj
T*
