(## 3.4 Brain Tumor Detection) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.4.1 Types of Brain Tumors in MRI) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Primary tumors \(originating in the brain\):**) Tj
T*
(- Glioblastoma Multiforme \(GBM\) ? Grade IV, most aggressive; heterogeneous enhancement on T1c;) Tj
T*
(central necrosis) Tj
T*
(- Low-grade glioma ? Grades II?III; T2/FLAIR hyperintense; minimal enhancement) Tj
T*
(- Meningioma ? Extra-axial; strong enhancement on T1c) Tj
T*
(- Medulloblastoma ? Posterior fossa; pediatric) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Secondary \(metastatic\):**  ) Tj
T*
(- Ring-enhancing lesions on T1c; often multiple; surrounded by vasogenic edema \(T2/FLAIR) Tj
T*
(bright\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.4.2 MRI Sequences for Brain Tumor Diagnosis) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The standard **multi-parametric MRI \(mpMRI\)** protocol for brain tumors includes:) Tj
T*
(- **T1 \(pre-contrast\):** Baseline anatomy; hemorrhage appears bright) Tj
T*
(- **T1c \(post-gadolinium contrast\):** Blood-brain barrier breakdown shows enhancement; tumor) Tj
T*
(core) Tj
T*
(- **T2:** Peritumoral edema bright; shows tumor extent) Tj
T*
(- **T2-FLAIR:** Fluid suppressed; edema and infiltration clearly visible) Tj
T*
(- **DWI/ADC:** Cell density; tumor cellularity; differentiates abscess from tumor) Tj
T*
(- **MR Spectroscopy \(MRS\):** Choline? \(cell membrane turnover\), NAA? \(neuronal death\); Cho/Cr) Tj
T*
(and Cho/NAA ratios indicate malignancy) Tj
T*
(- **Perfusion MRI \(DSC, DCE\):** Blood volume and flow; rCBV elevated in high-grade tumor) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.4.3 Manual vs. Automated Segmentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Manual segmentation:** Radiologist draws tumor boundaries on each slice ? gold standard but) Tj
T*
(time-consuming \(1?4 hours per case\) and subject to inter-rater variability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**BraTS \(Brain Tumor Segmentation\) Challenge:**  ) Tj
T*
(An annual competition \(MICCAI\) providing a standardized dataset and evaluation for automated) Tj
T*
(tumor segmentation. Sub-regions:) Tj
T*
(- **Enhancing tumor \(ET\):** T1c-bright region \(active tumor\)) Tj
T*
(- **Tumor core \(TC\):** ET + necrosis) Tj
T*
(- **Whole tumor \(WT\):** TC + peritumoral edema) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.4.4 Deep Learning for Brain Tumor Segmentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**3D U-Net / U-Net variants:**  ) Tj
T*
(The current state of the art. Input: 4-channel volume \(T1, T1c, T2, FLAIR\). Output: 3-channel) Tj
T*
(probability map \(ET, TC, WT regions\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Attention U-Net:**  ) Tj
T*
(Adds attention gates on skip connections to focus on relevant regions; suppresses irrelevant) Tj
T*
(background activations.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Transformer-based models:**  ) Tj
T*
(- **Swin-UNet, TransBTS, nnFormer:** Use self-attention to capture long-range dependencies) Tj
T*
(\(important for irregular tumor shapes\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Training considerations:**) Tj
T*
(- Class imbalance: tumor voxels ? 1?2% of total; use weighted loss, focal loss, or oversampling) Tj
T*
ET
