(## 4.1 Bzier Curves) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.1 History and Context) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The Bzier curve is named after **Pierre Bzier** \(1910?1999\), a French engineer at Renault,) Tj
T*
(who used them in the 1960s for designing car body shapes. The mathematical basis ? **Bernstein) Tj
T*
(polynomials** ? was established earlier by Sergei Bernstein in 1912. **Paul de Casteljau**) Tj
T*
(independently developed his algorithm at Citron in 1959, which remained a trade secret until) Tj
T*
(the 1980s.) Tj
T*
() Tj
