T*
(### 4.1.2 Control Points and the Curve) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A Bzier curve of **degree n** is defined by **n+1 control points** P?, P?, ..., P?.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The curve B\(t\) traces a path for t ? [0, 1]:) Tj
T*
(- B\(0\) = P? \(the curve always starts at the first control point\)) Tj
T*
(- B\(1\) = P? \(the curve always ends at the last control point\)) Tj
T*
(- Intermediate control points "attract" but don't lie on the curve \(in general\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.3 Bernstein Polynomial Form) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Bernstein basis polynomial of degree n:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B?,?\(t\) = C\(n,i\)  t?  \(1?t\)^\(n?i\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(where C\(n,i\) = n! / \(i! \(n?i\)!\) is the binomial coefficient.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Bzier curve formula:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(t\) = ????? B?,?\(t\)  P?) Tj
T*
(     = ????? C\(n,i\)  t?  \(1?t\)^\(n?i\)  P?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.4 Cases by Degree) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Linear \(n=1\) ? 2 control points:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(t\) = \(1?t\)P? + tP?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(This is simple linear interpolation. The curve is a straight line segment.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Quadratic \(n=2\) ? 3 control points:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(t\) = \(1?t\)P? + 2\(1?t\)tP? + tP?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bernstein weights: \(1?t\), 2t\(1?t\), t  ) Tj
T*
(These sum to 1: [\(1?t\) + t] = 1 ?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The curve passes through P? and P?, and is "pulled toward" P?.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Cubic \(n=3\) ? 4 control points:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(t\) = \(1?t\)P? + 3\(1?t\)tP? + 3\(1?t\)tP? + tP?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bernstein weights: \(1?t\), 3\(1?t\)t, 3\(1?t\)t, t  ) Tj
T*
(These sum to 1: [\(1?t\) + t] = 1 ?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Cubic Bzier curves are the most common in practice \(Adobe Illustrator, font outlines, CSS) Tj
T*
(animations\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**General \(arbitrary n\):**  ) Tj
T*
