T*
() Tj
T*
(| Degree | Coefficients | Formula |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| 1 | 1 1 | \(1?t\) t |) Tj
T*
(| 2 | 1 2 1 | \(1?t\) 2\(1?t\)t t |) Tj
T*
(| 3 | 1 3 3 1 | \(1?t\) 3\(1?t\)t 3\(1?t\)t t |) Tj
T*
(| 4 | 1 4 6 4 1 | \(1?t\)? ... t? |) Tj
T*
(| 5 | 1 5 10 10 5 1 | \(1?t\)? ... t? |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(\(Pascal's triangle gives the binomial coefficients\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.5 Properties of Bzier Curves) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Property | Description |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Endpoint interpolation | B\(0\) = P?, B\(1\) = P? |) Tj
T*
(| Convex hull property | Entire curve lies within convex hull of control points |) Tj
T*
(| Affine invariance | Transform control points ? same as transforming curve |) Tj
T*
(| Tangent at endpoints | B'\(0\) = n\(P??P?\); B'\(1\) = n\(P??P???\) |) Tj
T*
(| Variation diminishing | Curve crosses any line no more times than the control polygon does |) Tj
T*
(| Symmetry | Reversing control point order gives the same curve reversed |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Tangent at t=0:**  ) Tj
T*
(B'\(0\) = n\(P? ? P?\) ? the curve is tangent to the first edge of the control polygon) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Tangent at t=1:**  ) Tj
T*
(B'\(1\) = n\(P? ? P???\) ? the curve is tangent to the last edge) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These properties enable **C1 continuity** between two Bzier segments if you align P?, P?, and) Tj
T*
(Q? \(first control point of next curve\) collinearly: P? ? P??? = Q? ? Q?.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.6 Derivative Formula) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The first derivative of a degree-n Bzier curve is a degree-\(n-1\) Bzier curve:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B'\(t\) = n  ????^\(n?1\) B?,???\(t\)  \(P??? ? P?\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The second derivative:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B''\(t\) = n\(n-1\)  ????^\(n?2\) B?,???\(t\)  \(P??? ? 2P??? + P?\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1.7 Composite Bzier Curves \(Splines\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A single high-degree curve is hard to control. In practice, multiple cubic segments are joined:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- **C0 continuity:** Endpoint of curve i = start of curve i+1 \(no gap\)) Tj
T*
(- **C1 continuity:** Equal first derivatives \(tangent direction AND magnitude match\)) Tj
T*
(- **G1 continuity:** Equal tangent direction only \(not magnitude\); visually smooth junction) Tj
T*
(- **C2 continuity:** Equal second derivatives \(curvature matches\); smoother but more) Tj
T*
(constrained) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4.2 Bzier Surfaces) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2.1 Extension to 2D Parameter Space) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A Bzier surface of degree \(m, n\) is defined by a **\(m+1\)  \(n+1\) grid of control points**) Tj
T*
(P?,?.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It maps two parameters \(u, v\) ? [0,1] to a 3D point:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
