(B\(u,v\) = ????? ????? B?,?\(u\)  B?,?\(v\)  P?,?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(where B?,?\(u\) is the Bernstein basis in u-direction, and B?,?\(v\) is the Bernstein basis in) Tj
T*
(v-direction.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Interpretation:** Fix u ? you get a Bzier curve in v-direction with control points Q?\(u\) =) Tj
T*
(?? B?,?\(u\) P?,?. Varying v traces a Bzier curve through those moving control points.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2.2 Bicubic Bzier Patch \(Most Common\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Degree \(3,3\): 44 = **16 control points**, parameters \(u, v\) ? [0,1]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(u,v\) = ???? ???? B_{i,3}\(u\)  B_{j,3}\(v\)  P_{i,j}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Written in matrix form:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(u,v\) = U  M  P  M?  V?) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(where:) Tj
T*
(- U = [u, u, u, 1]) Tj
T*
(- V = [v, v, v, 1]) Tj
T*
(- M is the 44 Bzier basis matrix:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(M = [ -1  3 -3  1 ]) Tj
T*
(    [  3 -6  3  0 ]) Tj
T*
(    [ -3  3  0  0 ]) Tj
T*
(    [  1  0  0  0 ]) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(- P is the 443 control point matrix) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2.3 Properties) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(All properties of Bzier curves extend to surfaces:) Tj
T*
(- **Endpoint interpolation:** B\(0,0\) = P?,? etc. \(corner points are on the surface\)) Tj
T*
(- **Edge curves:** B\(0,v\) is a Bzier curve through control points P?,?, P?,?, P?,?, P?,?) Tj
T*
(- **Convex hull:** Surface lies within convex hull of control points) Tj
T*
(- **Partial derivatives \(tangent planes\):**  ) Tj
T*
(  ?B/?u\(0,0\) = 3\(P?,? ? P?,?\) ? tangent in u-direction at corner  ) Tj
T*
(  ?B/?v\(0,0\) = 3\(P?,? ? P?,?\) ? tangent in v-direction at corner  ) Tj
T*
(  Normal = \(?B/?u\)  \(?B/?v\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2.4 Evaluating a Point on the Surface) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Method:** Apply De Casteljau in u-direction to get intermediate control points, then apply De) Tj
T*
(Casteljau in v-direction \(or vice versa\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Algorithm:**) Tj
T*
(1. Fix u?. For each row i \(i = 0..m\), evaluate the Bzier curve Q?\(u?\) = De Casteljau on row i) Tj
T*
(at parameter u?. This gives \(n+1\) intermediate points {Q?, Q?, ..., Q?}.) Tj
T*
(2. Fix v?. Apply De Casteljau on {Q?, ..., Q?} at parameter v?. The result is B\(u?, v?\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4.3 De Casteljau's Algorithm) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.1 Motivation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(While the Bernstein polynomial formula is mathematically clean, direct evaluation requires) Tj
T*
(computing large binomial coefficients \(e.g., C\(20,10\) = 184,756 for a degree-20 curve\) and is) Tj
T*
(numerically unstable for high degrees.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(De Casteljau's algorithm avoids these issues:) Tj
T*
ET
