BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
(- No large numbers) Tj
T*
(- Numerically stable \(each step is just a linear interpolation\)) Tj
T*
(- Also provides curve subdivision as a byproduct) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.2 The Algorithm) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Given control points P?, P?, ..., P? and parameter t? ? [0,1]:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Initialize:** Set P???? = P? for i = 0, 1, ..., n) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Recurrence relation:**) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(P???? = \(1 ? t?\)  P????? + t?  P???????) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(for j = 1, 2, ..., n and i = 0, 1, ..., n?j) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Result:** B\(t?\) = P????) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Each step linearly interpolates between adjacent points with ratio t?. After n rounds, one) Tj
T*
(point remains ? that is the curve point.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.3 Triangular Scheme \(Hand Calculation Table\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The computation can be organized in a triangular table:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(j=0        j=1          j=2          j=3 \(result\)) Tj
T*
(P????) Tj
T*
(          P???) Tj
T*
(P????              P???) Tj
T*
(          P???                P??? ? Answer) Tj
T*
(P????              P???) Tj
T*
(          P???) Tj
T*
(P????) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Each entry is the linear interpolation of its two upper-left neighbors.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.4 Geometric Interpretation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Each iteration shrinks the polygon by linear interpolation. The intermediate points at each) Tj
T*
(level form a new control polygon. The key insight:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- At parameter t?, the leftmost column of the triangular table {P????, P???, ..., P????} gives) Tj
T*
(control points for the LEFT sub-curve B?\(t\) for t ? [0, t?]) Tj
T*
(- The diagonal {P????, P?????, ..., P????} gives control points for the RIGHT sub-curve B?\(t\)) Tj
T*
(for t ? [t?, 1]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is **curve subdivision** ? splitting one curve into two Bzier curves at any parameter) Tj
T*
(value.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.5 Pseudocode) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```python) Tj
T*
(def de_casteljau\(points, t\):) Tj
T*
(    """) Tj
T*
(    points: list of control points [[x0,y0], [x1,y1], ..., [xn,yn]]) Tj
T*
(    t: parameter in [0,1]) Tj
T*
(    returns: point on curve at parameter t) Tj
T*
(    """) Tj
T*
(    p = [list\(pt\) for pt in points]  # copy) Tj
T*
(    n = len\(p\) - 1) Tj
T*
(    for j in range\(1, n + 1\):) Tj
T*
ET
