(        for i in range\(n - j + 1\):) Tj
T*
(            p[i][0] = \(1 - t\) * p[i][0] + t * p[i+1][0]) Tj
T*
(            p[i][1] = \(1 - t\) * p[i][1] + t * p[i+1][1]) Tj
T*
(    return p[0]) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.3.6 Complexity) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- For a degree-n curve: n + \(n?1\) + ... + 1 = n\(n+1\)/2 linear interpolations) Tj
T*
(- Each linear interpolation is O\(1\) operations per coordinate) Tj
T*
(- Total: O\(n\) per evaluation) Tj
T*
(- Compared to direct Bernstein: also O\(n\) but with better numerical properties) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4.4 Worked Computation Examples) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(> These are the types of computation questions expected in the exam.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Example 1: Quadratic Bzier Curve at t = 0.75) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Given:** Control points P? = \(0, 0\), P? = \(1, 2\), P? = \(3, 0\)  ) Tj
T*
(**Find:** B\(0.75\)) Tj
T*
