(> *A 3D point cloud is an unordered set of 3D coordinates with no topology. Triangulation) Tj
T*
(converts it into a triangle mesh by inferring surface connectivity. The Ball Pivoting Algorithm) Tj
T*
(\(BPA\) places a virtual sphere of radius ?; as the sphere rolls over the points, each contact) Tj
T*
(with a third point creates a triangle. Alternatively, Poisson Surface Reconstruction treats the) Tj
T*
(problem globally: it estimates point normals, constructs a vector field, and solves a Poisson) Tj
T*
(equation ?? = ?V whose isosurface is the reconstructed mesh. Applications include 3D) Tj
T*
(scanning, medical image visualization, and heritage preservation.*) Tj
