(### 2.3 Robustness pitfalls \(great exam bonus\)) Tj
T*
(- Nearly cocircular points -> floating point ambiguity) Tj
T*
(- Collinear subsets -> degenerate triangles) Tj
T*
(- Duplicate points -> broken predicates) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Mitigations:) Tj
T*
(- symbolic perturbation / exact predicates \(Shewchuk-style orientation/in-circle\)) Tj
T*
(- epsilon-aware duplicate filtering) Tj
T*
(- deterministic tie-breaks) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 2.4 Complexity statements to memorize) Tj
T*
(- Bowyer-Watson expected: O\(n log n\)) Tj
T*
(- Worst-case for many practical incremental methods: O\(n^2\)) Tj
T*
(- Planar triangulation edge count \(general position\): about 3n - 3 - h) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3\) Marching Cubes: Topology-Correct Thinking) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.1 Core idea \(exam-safe wording\)) Tj
T*
(Given a scalar field sampled at grid corners, classify each cube corner against an isovalue,) Tj
T*
(then emit triangles from a lookup table and interpolate vertex positions on intersected edges.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.2 Interpolation formula) Tj
T*
(t = \(iso - f1\) / \(f2 - f1\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(p = p1 + t \(p2 - p1\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.3 Ambiguity handling hierarchy) Tj
T*
(1. Original MC \(15 symmetry classes\)) Tj
T*
(2. Asymptotic Decider \(face ambiguity resolution\)) Tj
T*
(3. MC33 \(topology-aware case expansion\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.4 Normal computation for shading) Tj
T*
(- Analytical: normal = gradient of trilinear field) Tj
T*
(- Practical finite difference:) Tj
T*
(  - fx ~ f\(x+1\)-f\(x-1\)) Tj
T*
(  - fy ~ f\(y+1\)-f\(y-1\)) Tj
T*
(  - fz ~ f\(z+1\)-f\(z-1\)) Tj
T*
(- Normalize and interpolate to vertices) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.5 Practical mesh quality improvements) Tj
T*
(- Deduplicate edge vertices with hash map keyed by \(cell,edge\)) Tj
T*
(- Apply Taubin/Laplacian smoothing cautiously \(avoid volume shrink\)) Tj
T*
(- Use manifold checks before downstream FEM/printing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
