() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. VR Core Requirements) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 6 Degrees of Freedom \(6-DoF\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Translation:  X \(left/right\), Y \(up/down\), Z \(forward/back\)) Tj
T*
(Rotation:     Pitch \(nod\), Yaw \(shake head\), Roll \(tilt\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(All 6 must be tracked in real time to avoid motion sickness.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Performance Requirements) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Metric | Minimum | Target | Premium |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Frame rate | 60 fps | 90 fps | 120 fps |) Tj
T*
(| Latency \(motion-to-photon\) | 20 ms | 10 ms | 7 ms |) Tj
T*
(| Resolution \(per eye\) | 1600x1440 | 2064x2208 | 4K+ |) Tj
T*
(| Field of View | 90 deg | 110 deg | 120+ deg |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Why < 20ms Latency Matters) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The vestibular system detects head movement within 2-5ms. The visual system must confirm) Tj
T*
(the movement within ~20ms or the mismatch causes simulator sickness \(nausea, disorientation\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. VR Tracking Technologies) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Inside-Out Tracking \(Modern Standard\)) Tj
T*
(- Cameras on the HMD observe the environment) Tj
T*
(- SLAM/VIO algorithms compute device pose from observed features) Tj
T*
(- No external infrastructure needed) Tj
T*
(- Devices: Meta Quest 2/3/Pro, HoloLens 2, Apple Vision Pro) Tj
T*
(- Accuracy: 1-3mm position, <0.1 degree rotation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Outside-In Tracking \(High-End PC VR\)) Tj
T*
(- External base stations emit IR laser sweeps \(Lighthouse tracking\)) Tj
T*
(- Sensors on HMD and controllers triangulate position) Tj
T*
(- Devices: Valve Index, HTC Vive, HTC Vive Pro) Tj
T*
(- Accuracy: <1mm position \(more precise than inside-out\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### IMU \(Inertial Measurement Unit\)) Tj
T*
(- All HMDs include IMU: accelerometer + gyroscope) Tj
T*
(- Provides high-frequency \(1000 Hz\) rotation data) Tj
T*
(- Fused with camera data via Extended Kalman Filter \(EKF\)) Tj
T*
(- Alone: fast but drifts over time; with vision: stable) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Visual-Inertial Odometry \(VIO\)) Tj
T*
(The gold standard. Camera provides absolute position via feature matching.) Tj
T*
(IMU provides 1000 Hz rotation between video frames \(30-60 fps\).) Tj
T*
(EKF/Kalman filter fuses them: accurate, drift-corrected, low-latency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ORB-SLAM3 \(arXiv:2007.11898\) is the state-of-the-art open-source VIO system:) Tj
T*
(- Features: ORB \(Oriented FAST + Rotated BRIEF\) - fast and rotation invariant) Tj
T*
(- MAP estimation: optimizes all poses + map points jointly) Tj
T*
(- Multi-map: when tracking lost, starts new sub-map; later merges) Tj
T*
(- Accuracy: 3.6cm on EuRoC drone dataset, 9mm hand-held) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. VR Display Technologies) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
