(### OLED vs LCD) Tj
T*
(| Property | OLED | LCD |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Black level | True black \(pixel off\) | Backlit \(gray black\) |) Tj
T*
(| Contrast | Very high \(1,000,000:1\) | Lower \(1,000:1\) |) Tj
T*
(| Response time | <0.1ms | 1-5ms \(ghosting risk\) |) Tj
T*
(| Burn-in | Yes \(static images\) | No |) Tj
T*
(| Brightness | Lower | Higher |) Tj
T*
(| Used in | PSVR2, Valve Index | Meta Quest 2 |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Optics Types) Tj
T*
(- Fresnel: Concentric rings; wide FoV; light; some god-rays) Tj
T*
(- Pancake: Multiple reflective surfaces; thin/compact; dimmer) Tj
T*
(  \(Meta Quest 3, Apple Vision Pro use pancake\)) Tj
T*
(- Catadioptric: Hybrid reflective; used in Varjo headsets) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Vergence-Accommodation Conflict \(VAC\)) Tj
T*
(Eyes converge \(rotate\) to virtual object depth but must accommodate \(focus lens\)) Tj
T*
(to fixed screen distance \(~2m optical\). Causes eye strain in prolonged use.) Tj
T*
(Solutions:) Tj
T*
(- Varifocal displays: Mechanically move lens based on eye tracking) Tj
T*
(- Light field displays: Multiple focal planes \(computational lightfield\)) Tj
T*
(- Holographic displays: Wave optics, true 3D light field \(future\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Rendering Techniques for VR) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Foveated Rendering) Tj
T*
(- Fovea \(center of retina\): 2 degrees, maximum acuity) Tj
T*
(- Periphery: 80% of visual field but 50% lower acuity) Tj
T*
(- With eye tracking: render only foveal region at full quality) Tj
T*
(- Periphery: 25-50% lower resolution \(user cannot detect\)) Tj
T*
(- GPU savings: 3-5x reduction in shading cost) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Devices with eye tracking: Apple Vision Pro, PlayStation VR2, Varjo headsets) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Asynchronous Spacewarp \(ASW\) / Timewarp) Tj
T*
(If GPU drops below 90 fps: instead of judder \(dropped frame\), the runtime) Tj
T*
(extrapolates the next frame by warping the last rendered frame using depth + motion.) Tj
T*
(User perceives smooth 90fps even if game renders at 45fps.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Single-Pass Stereo Rendering) Tj
T*
(Render both eyes in one draw call using:) Tj
T*
(- Geometry shaders \(instancing to two render targets\)) Tj
T*
(- Multi-view extension \(GL_OVR_multiview, VK_KHR_multiview\)) Tj
T*
(- Reduces CPU-GPU draw call overhead by ~40%) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Lens Distortion Pre-correction) Tj
T*
(Fresnel lenses create barrel distortion \(edges bow outward\).) Tj
T*
(Renderer applies inverse pincushion distortion to the image.) Tj
T*
(The lens then corrects it back to a straight image.) Tj
T*
(Separate distortion maps for R, G, B channels to correct chromatic aberration.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. AR: How It Works) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Three Core Problems) Tj
T*
(1. TRACKING: Know device pose \(6-DoF\) in real world at all times) Tj
T*
(2. REGISTRATION: Align virtual content precisely to real world coordinates \(pixel-perfect\)) Tj
T*
(3. RENDERING: Blend virtual content with real world \(occlusion, lighting, shadows\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Marker-Based AR Pipeline) Tj
T*
