T*
() Tj
T*
(# Delaunay Triangulation --- Complete Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(> Wikipedia says: "A Delaunay triangulation of a set of points in the plane subdivides their) Tj
T*
(convex hull into triangles whose circumcircles do not contain any of the points. This maximizes) Tj
T*
(the size of the smallest angle in any of the triangles, and tends to avoid sliver triangles.") Tj
T*
(> Named after Boris Delaunay for his work from 1934.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. The Core Definition) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
