71 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 70 0 R >>
endobj
72 0 obj
<< /Length 2782 >>
stream
BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
(**Circumcircle Property:** For every triangle in the Delaunay triangulation, the circumcircle) Tj
T*
(\(the unique circle passing through all 3 vertices\) contains NO other input point in its) Tj
T*
(interior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If any point P lies inside the circumcircle of triangle ABC, then ABC is NOT a valid Delaunay) Tj
T*
(triangle and must be "flipped.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### The Circumcircle Test \(Determinant\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Given triangle A,B,C \(counterclockwise\) and test point D:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(|Ax-Dx  Ay-Dy  \(Ax-Dx\)^2+\(Ay-Dy\)^2|) Tj
T*
(|Bx-Dx  By-Dy  \(Bx-Dx\)^2+\(By-Dy\)^2| > 0  =>  D is INSIDE circumcircle) Tj
T*
(|Cx-Dx  Cy-Dy  \(Cx-Dx\)^2+\(Cy-Dy\)^2|) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If determinant > 0: D inside circle => NOT Delaunay => flip edge) Tj
T*
(If determinant < 0: D outside circle => OK) Tj
T*
(If determinant = 0: D ON circle => ambiguous \(degenerate\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Key Properties) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. **Maximizes minimum angle** -- the "fattest" triangles possible) Tj
T*
(2. **Avoids slivers** -- no long thin triangles \(numerically bad for FEA, rendering\)) Tj
T*
(3. **Unique** -- for n points in general position \(no 4 points cocircular\)) Tj
T*
(4. **Dual of Voronoi diagram** -- connect circumcenters of adjacent triangles => Voronoi edges) Tj
T*
(5. **Count** -- at most 2n-h-2 triangles \(n=points, h=convex hull vertices\)) Tj
T*
(6. **Geometric spanner** -- shortest path along edges is at most 1.998x Euclidean distance) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Voronoi Duality) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Voronoi cell of point p = region closer to p than any other point.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Delaunay <-> Voronoi duality:**) Tj
T*
(- Delaunay vertex = Voronoi cell center) Tj
T*
(- Delaunay edge AB = dual Voronoi edge \(perpendicular bisector of AB between Vor\(A\) and Vor\(B\)\)) Tj
T*
(- Delaunay triangle circumcenter = Voronoi vertex) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Building one from the other is O\(n\) after first construction.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. The Edge Flip Operation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Given two triangles sharing edge BD \(forming quadrilateral ABCD\):) Tj
T*
(- If the sum of opposite angles alpha + gamma > 180 degrees, edge BD is "illegal") Tj
T*
(- Flip BD to AC => creates two new triangles that satisfy Delaunay condition) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Before flip:           After flip:) Tj
T*
(    A                      A) Tj
T*
(   /|\\                    /|) Tj
T*
(  / | \\                  / |) Tj
T*
( /  BD  \\               /  |) Tj
T*
(B---+---C    =>      B  AC  C) Tj
T*
( \\  |  /               \\  |) Tj
T*
(  \\ | /                 \\ |) Tj
T*
(   \\|/                   \\|) Tj
T*
(    D                      D) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
