(# Source: marching_cubes.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# Marching Cubes --- Complete Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(> Wikipedia says: "Marching cubes is a computer graphics algorithm, published in the 1987) Tj
T*
(SIGGRAPH proceedings by Lorensen and Cline, for extracting a polygonal mesh of an isosurface) Tj
T*
(from a three-dimensional discrete scalar field.") Tj
T*
(> "The applications are mainly concerned with medical visualizations such as CT and MRI scan) Tj
T*
(data images.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Input:** 3D scalar field f\(x,y,z\) sampled on a regular grid \(voxels\)) Tj
T*
(         e.g., CT scan \(Hounsfield units\), MRI intensity, distance field) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Output:** Triangle mesh of the isosurface {\(x,y,z\) : f\(x,y,z\) = isovalue}) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Example:** Extract a brain surface from MRI by thresholding at the grey matter / CSF) Tj
T*
(boundary.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Algorithm Steps) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(For each 2x2x2 voxel cube in the grid:) Tj
T*
(  1. CLASSIFY: Label each of 8 corners as inside \(f > isovalue\) or outside \(f <= isovalue\)) Tj
T*
(  ) Tj
T*
(  2. INDEX: Convert 8 binary labels to an 8-bit integer \(index 0..255\)) Tj
T*
(     bit 0 = corner 0, bit 1 = corner 1, ..., bit 7 = corner 7) Tj
T*
(  ) Tj
T*
(  3. LOOKUP: Use triTable[index] to get the list of triangle edges \(up to 5 triangles\)) Tj
T*
(  ) Tj
T*
(  4. INTERPOLATE: For each triangle edge crossing the isosurface, linearly interpolate:) Tj
T*
(     t = \(isovalue - f\(v1\)\) / \(f\(v2\) - f\(v1\)\)) Tj
T*
(     vertex = v1 + t * \(v2 - v1\)) Tj
T*
(  ) Tj
T*
(  5. OUTPUT: Store triangle vertices) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. The 256 Cases -> 15 Unique Cases) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
