endobj
78 0 obj
<< /Length 2354 >>
stream
BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
() Tj
T*
(By exploiting rotational and reflective symmetry, all 256 possible corner configurations) Tj
T*
(reduce to 15 unique cases:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Case 0:  All outside -> no triangles) Tj
T*
(Case 1:  1 corner inside -> 1 triangle \(corner cut\)) Tj
T*
(Case 2:  2 adjacent corners inside -> 1 triangle) Tj
T*
(Case 3:  2 diagonal corners inside -> 2 triangles \(ambiguous!\)) Tj
T*
(Case 4:  1 corner inside \(opposite side\) -> 1 triangle) Tj
T*
(Case 5:  3 corners of a face inside -> 2 triangles) Tj
T*
(...) Tj
T*
(Case 14: 7 corners inside \(1 outside\) -> 1 triangle \(complement of case 1\)) Tj
T*
(Case 15: All inside -> no triangles) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The original paper had 15 cases \(reduced by symmetry\).) Tj
T*
(Marching Cubes 33 \(Chernyaev 1995\) expands to 33 cases to resolve topological ambiguities.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Linear Interpolation Along Edges) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When an edge crosses the isosurface:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(t = \(isovalue - f_v1\) / \(f_v2 - f_v1\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(vertex = v1 + t * \(v2 - v1\)) Tj
T*
(       = \(1-t\)*v1 + t*v2) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This places the vertex at the exact isovalue crossing within the edge.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Example:** edge from \(0,0,0\) with f=10 to \(1,0,0\) with f=30, isovalue=20:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(t = \(20 - 10\) / \(30 - 10\) = 10/20 = 0.5) Tj
T*
(vertex = \(0,0,0\) + 0.5 * \(1,0,0\) = \(0.5, 0, 0\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Normal Estimation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The gradient of the scalar field gives the surface normal at each vertex:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(N\(x,y,z\) = grad\(f\) = \(df/dx, df/dy, df/dz\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Finite differences:) Tj
T*
(df/dx ~ \(f\(x+1,y,z\) - f\(x-1,y,z\)\) / 2) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Interpolate normals from grid vertices to triangle vertices the same way as positions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. Ambiguous Cases and Marching Cubes 33) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Face ambiguity:** When opposite corners of a cube face are both inside/outside,) Tj
T*
(the surface crossing pattern is ambiguous \(two valid triangulations\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Interior ambiguity:** Even with face ambiguities resolved, some cube configurations) Tj
T*
(have multiple valid interior triangulations.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
