(# Source: mri_ct_scanning.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# MRI and CT Scanning --- Complete Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(> Wikipedia on MRI: "Magnetic resonance imaging \(MRI\) is a medical imaging technique used in) Tj
T*
(radiology to generate pictures of the anatomy and the physiological processes inside the body.) Tj
T*
(MRI scanners use strong magnetic fields, magnetic field gradients, and radio waves to form) Tj
T*
(images of the organs in the body. MRI does not involve X-rays or the use of ionizing radiation,) Tj
T*
(which distinguishes it from computed tomography \(CT\) and positron emission tomography \(PET\)) Tj
T*
(scans.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. CT Scanning \(Computed Tomography\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Physical Principle) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(X-ray CT uses ionizing radiation \(X-rays\). As X-rays pass through tissue they are absorbed:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(I = I0 * exp\(-Integral[mu\(x\)] dx\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(where mu\(x\) is the linear attenuation coefficient. CT reconstructs the 3D map of mu\(x,y,z\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Hounsfield Units \(HU\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Standardized scale of CT attenuation:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(HU = 1000 * \(mu_tissue - mu_water\) / \(mu_water - mu_air\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Tissue | HU Range |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Air | -1000 |) Tj
T*
(| Lung | -900 to -500 |) Tj
T*
(| Fat | -120 to -80 |) Tj
T*
(| Water / CSF | 0 |) Tj
T*
(| White matter | +20 to +30 |) Tj
T*
(| Grey matter | +35 to +45 |) Tj
T*
(| Blood | +50 to +80 |) Tj
T*
(| Liver | +40 to +65 |) Tj
T*
(| Calcification/bone | +100 to +1900 |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### CT Windowing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Display a range of HU values mapped to 0-255 gray:) Tj
T*
(- Window Level \(WL\) = center of the range) Tj
T*
(- Window Width \(WW\) = width of the range) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Window | WL | WW | Shows |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Brain | 40 | 80 | Grey/white matter |) Tj
T*
(| Bone | 400 | 1800 | Bone detail |) Tj
T*
(| Lung | -600 | 1500 | Lung parenchyma |) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
