<< /Length 2400 >>
stream
BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
(| Abdomen | 60 | 400 | Soft tissue organs |) Tj
T*
(| Stroke | 40 | 40 | Acute hemorrhage |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### CT Reconstruction: Filtered Back-Projection \(FBP\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CT acquisition = measuring the Radon transform \(line integrals\):) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(R_theta\(s\) = Integral[ mu\(x,y\) * delta\(x*cos\(theta\) + y*sin\(theta\) - s\) ] dx dy) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(FBP Algorithm:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(1. For each angle theta:) Tj
T*
(   a. Acquire projection p_theta\(s\)) Tj
T*
(   b. Fourier transform: P_hat\(f\) = FT[p_theta\(s\)]) Tj
T*
(   c. Apply ramp filter: P_filtered\(f\) = |f| * P_hat\(f\)) Tj
T*
(   d. Inverse FT: p_filtered\(s\) = IFT[P_filtered\(f\)]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Back-project:) Tj
T*
(   mu\(x,y\) = Integral_0^pi  p_filtered\(x*cos\(theta\) + y*sin\(theta\)\) d\(theta\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The ramp filter |f| compensates for the 1/f density of back-projected data.) Tj
T*
(In practice multiplied by Hamming/Hann window to reduce noise:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(H\(f\) = |f| * \(0.54 + 0.46*cos\(pi*f/fmax\)\)   [Hamming-windowed ramp]) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Iterative Reconstruction \(IR\) -- Modern CT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Model system as Ax = b:) Tj
T*
(- x = unknown attenuation image \(vectorized\)) Tj
T*
(- b = measured projections) Tj
T*
(- A = system matrix \(each row = one ray integral\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solve iteratively:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(x_{k+1} = x_k - alpha * A^T * \(A*x_k - b\) + regularization) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Benefits: 50-80% dose reduction for same image quality.) Tj
T*
(All modern scanners use IR: Siemens SAFIRE, GE ASIR, Philips iDose.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. MRI Scanning) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Nuclear Magnetic Resonance Physics) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Hydrogen nuclei \(protons\) in magnetic field B0 precess at Larmor frequency:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(f0 = gamma * B0 / \(2*pi\)) Tj
T*
(gamma = 42.577 MHz/T for proton) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(At B0 = 1.5T: f0 = 63.87 MHz) Tj
T*
(At B0 = 3.0T: f0 = 127.74 MHz \(radio frequency band\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### The Three Stages of MRI) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. ALIGNMENT: B0 creates net magnetization M0 along z-axis) Tj
T*
(   \(1 in ~10^6 spins excess at body temperature\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. EXCITATION: RF pulse at f0 tips magnetization:) Tj
T*
(   - 90 degree pulse: M tips fully into transverse \(xy\) plane) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
85 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 84 0 R >>
endobj
86 0 obj
<< /Length 2929 >>
stream
BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
(   - 180 degree pulse: M flips) Tj
T*
(   After excitation, precessing M induces voltage in receive coil -> MRI signal) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. RELAXATION:) Tj
T*
(   T1 recovery \(longitudinal\):  Mz\(t\) = M0 * \(1 - exp\(-t/T1\)\)) Tj
T*
(   T2 decay \(transverse\):       Mxy\(t\) = Mxy0 * exp\(-t/T2\)) Tj
T*
(   T2* decay \(with inhomogeneity\): faster than T2) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### T1 and T2 Times for Brain Tissues \(at 3T\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Tissue | T1 \(ms\) | T2 \(ms\) |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| White matter | 1110 | 69 |) Tj
T*
(| Grey matter | 1820 | 99 |) Tj
T*
(| CSF | 4000 | 2200 |) Tj
T*
(| Fat | 365 | 133 |) Tj
T*
(| Tumor \(glioma\) | 1500-2000 | 100-200 |) Tj
T*
(| Edema | 1900 | 150 |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Spatial Encoding: k-Space) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Gradient coils add spatially varying field to B0:) Tj
T*
(- Gz \(slice selection\): only slice where B0+Gz*z = f0/gamma excited) Tj
T*
(- Gy \(phase encoding\): phase of Mxy varies with y position) Tj
T*
(- Gx \(frequency encoding\): precession frequency varies with x during readout) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Data acquired in k-space \(spatial frequency domain\):) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(kx = gamma/\(2*pi\) * Integral[Gx\(t\) dt]) Tj
T*
(ky = gamma/\(2*pi\) * Integral[Gy\(t\) dt]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Signal\(kx,ky\) = FT[proton_density\(x,y\)] \(Fourier transform of image!\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Image reconstruction: 2D Inverse Fourier Transform of k-space data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(k-Space properties:) Tj
T*
(- Center: low frequencies -> overall brightness and contrast) Tj
T*
(- Edges: high frequencies -> fine detail and edges) Tj
T*
(- If only center acquired: blurry but fast \(cardiac MRI uses this\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### MRI Sequences and Contrast) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(By varying TR \(repetition time\) and TE \(echo time\):) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Sequence | TR | TE | Bright | Dark | Clinical Use |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| T1-weighted | Short \(<800ms\) | Short \(<30ms\) | Fat, gadolinium, white matter | CSF | Anatomy,) Tj
T*
(post-contrast |) Tj
T*
(| T2-weighted | Long \(>2000ms\) | Long \(>80ms\) | CSF, edema, most tumors | Fat | Pathology,) Tj
T*
(lesions |) Tj
T*
(| FLAIR | Long | Long | White matter lesions | CSF suppressed | MS, glioma, stroke |) Tj
T*
(| DWI | --- | --- | Restricted diffusion | Free diffusion | Stroke, abscess |) Tj
T*
(| T1+Gd | Short | Short | Enhancing regions | --- | Tumor vascularity, BBB breakdown |) Tj
T*
(| SWI | Long | Long | --- | Hemosiderin, deoxy-Hb | Bleeds, veins, iron |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Advanced MRI Techniques) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Diffusion Tensor Imaging \(DTI\):**) Tj
T*
(Measures diffusion anisotropy -> maps white matter tracts \(tractography\).) Tj
T*
(Pre-surgical planning: avoid eloquent white matter fibers.) Tj
T*
(ADC \(Apparent Diffusion Coefficient\): low in stroke, high-grade tumor.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Perfusion MRI \(DSC\):**) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
