(# Source: brain_tumor_detection.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# Brain Tumor Detection --- Complete Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Overview of Brain Tumors) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Classification) Tj
T*
(- Primary: Originate in brain tissue) Tj
T*
(  - Gliomas \(most common\): astrocytoma, glioblastoma \(GBM\), oligodendroglioma) Tj
T*
(  - Meningioma: from meninges, usually benign) Tj
T*
(  - Pituitary adenoma) Tj
T*
(  - Medulloblastoma \(pediatric\)) Tj
T*
(- Secondary \(metastatic\): Spread from elsewhere \(lung, breast, melanoma\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### WHO Grading \(2021 Classification\)) Tj
T*
(- Grade 1: Slow-growing, often resectable \(e.g., pilocytic astrocytoma\)) Tj
T*
(- Grade 2: Diffuse, infiltrating; low mitotic activity) Tj
T*
(- Grade 3: Malignant features, mitoses \(anaplastic glioma\)) Tj
T*
(- Grade 4: High mitotic activity, necrosis, microvascular proliferation \(GBM\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**GBM \(Glioblastoma Multiforme\):**) Tj
T*
(- Most common primary brain malignancy in adults) Tj
T*
(- Median survival: 14-16 months with maximal treatment) Tj
T*
(- Hallmarks: ring enhancement \(T1c\), central necrosis, peritumoral edema \(T2/FLAIR\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. BraTS Dataset and Challenge) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### International Brain Tumor Segmentation Challenge \(arXiv:1811.02629\)) Tj
T*
(Annual challenge at MICCAI \(premier medical image computing conference\).) Tj
T*
(Running since 2012. BraTS 2023: 1251 training cases.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Four MRI Modalities per Patient) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(T1:    Anatomy, structural details) Tj
T*
(T1ce:  Post-contrast; shows blood-brain barrier breakdown \(active tumor: BRIGHT\)) Tj
T*
(T2:    Edema and infiltration \(tumor + edema: BRIGHT\)) Tj
T*
(FLAIR: Edema without CSF \(tumor/edema: BRIGHT, CSF: DARK\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Tumor Sub-region Labels) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(BraTS uses 3 nested labels:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Whole Tumor \(WT\)  = everything: enhancing + necrosis + edema) Tj
T*
(Tumor Core \(TC\)   = enhancing + necrosis \(without edema\)) Tj
T*
(Enhancing Tumor \(ET\) = only the gadolinium-enhancing active tumor) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
