(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In voxel labels:) Tj
T*
(- Label 1: Necrotic core \(non-enhancing tumor core\)) Tj
T*
(- Label 2: Peritumoral edematous/invaded tissue) Tj
T*
(- Label 4: GD-enhancing tumor) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Evaluation Metrics) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Dice Score = 2*|prediction AND ground_truth| / \(|prediction| + |ground_truth|\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Range [0,1]. 1 = perfect. Typical state-of-the-art: ~0.90 WT, ~0.86 TC, ~0.83 ET.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Hausdorff Distance 95th percentile \(HD95\): Surface distance in mm.) Tj
T*
(State-of-the-art: ~3-5mm.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Clinical MRI Features for Brain Tumors) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Glioblastoma \(GBM\) - Grade 4) Tj
T*
(| Sequence | Appearance |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| T1 | Hypointense mass; may show isointense core |) Tj
T*
(| T1ce | RING ENHANCEMENT \(hallmark!\) around necrotic core |) Tj
T*
(| T2 | Hyperintense tumor + extensive surrounding edema |) Tj
T*
(| FLAIR | Hyperintense mass + edema; suppresses CSF |) Tj
T*
(| DWI | Rim of restricted diffusion \(high cellularity at enhancing border\) |) Tj
T*
(| ADC | Low ADC at enhancing rim; elevated in necrosis and edema |) Tj
T*
(| Perfusion \(rCBV\) | ELEVATED \(high vascularity = high grade\) |) Tj
T*
(| Spectroscopy | High Cho, low NAA, Lac+Lip peaks \(necrosis\) |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Lower Grade Glioma \(Grade 2-3\)) Tj
T*
(- T2/FLAIR: Hyperintense, diffusely infiltrating, no clear boundary) Tj
T*
(- T1ce: Little or no enhancement \(no BBB disruption\)) Tj
T*
(- DWI: Not usually restricted) Tj
T*
(- Spectroscopy: Mildly elevated Cho) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Metastases) Tj
T*
(- T1ce: SOLID RING or homogeneous enhancement) Tj
T*
(- T2: Variable; usually distinct spherical mass) Tj
T*
(- Multiple lesions: strongly suggests metastases over primary) Tj
T*
(- Located at grey-white matter junction \(blood-borne distribution\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Deep Learning for Brain Tumor Segmentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### U-Net for Brain Tumor Segmentation \(2015-\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(U-Net \(arXiv:1505.04597\) applied to brain tumor:) Tj
T*
(- Input: 4-channel volume \(T1, T1ce, T2, FLAIR\) concatenated) Tj
T*
(- 3D U-Net: processes volumetric data directly) Tj
T*
(- Output: Per-voxel class probability for 4 classes \(background + 3 tumor labels\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key adaptations for brain tumor:) Tj
T*
(- Residual connections within encoder/decoder blocks) Tj
T*
(- Deep supervision: loss at multiple decoder levels) Tj
T*
(- Patch-based training: random 128x128x128 patches) Tj
T*
(- Test-time augmentation: flip along all axes, average predictions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### nnU-Net \(2021\) - State of the Art) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Self-configuring U-Net that automatically determines:) Tj
T*
ET
