100 0 obj
<< /Length 2759 >>
stream
BT
/F1 9 Tf
11 TL
54 738 Td
(Rule: each number = sum of two numbers directly above it.) Tj
T*
(C\(n,i\) = C\(n-1,i-1\) + C\(n-1,i\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. Properties You Must Know) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Property | Formula/Explanation |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| **Endpoint interpolation** | B\(0\)=P?, B\(1\)=P? always |) Tj
T*
(| **Convex hull** | Entire curve lies within convex hull of control points |) Tj
T*
(| **Affine invariance** | Transform control points ? transforms curve identically |) Tj
T*
(| **Tangent at start** | B'\(0\) = n\(P? ? P?\) |) Tj
T*
(| **Tangent at end** | B'\(1\) = n\(P? ? P???\) |) Tj
T*
(| **Derivative is Bzier** | B'\(t\) is a Bzier of degree n?1 with ?P? = n\(P????P?\) |) Tj
T*
(| **Symmetry** | Reverse P? order ? same curve reversed |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 7. Derivatives) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**First derivative** \(itself a Bzier of degree n?1\):) Tj
T*
($$B'\(t\) = n \\sum_{i=0}^{n-1} B_{i,n-1}\(t\) \\cdot \(P_{i+1} - P_i\)$$) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Cubic first derivative** \(degree 2 Bzier with ?Ps\):) Tj
T*
($$B'\(t\) = 3[\(1-t\)^2\(P_1-P_0\) + 2t\(1-t\)\(P_2-P_1\) + t^2\(P_3-P_2\)]$$) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**At t=0:** $B'\(0\) = n\(P_1 - P_0\)$ \(tangent direction P??P?, magnitude n\)) Tj
T*
(**At t=1:** $B'\(1\) = n\(P_n - P_{n-1}\)$ \(tangent direction P????P?, magnitude n\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 8. Quick Evaluation at Special t Values) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### At t = 0.5) Tj
T*
(| Degree | Formula | Value |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Linear | \(P?+P?\)/2 | midpoint |) Tj
T*
(| Quadratic | \(P?+2P?+P?\)/4 | weighted average |) Tj
T*
(| Cubic | \(P?+3P?+3P?+P?\)/8 | weighted average |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### At t = 1/3) Tj
T*
(Coefficients for quadratic: \(1-1/3\)=4/9, 2\(1/3\)\(2/3\)=4/9, \(1/3\)=1/9) Tj
T*
($$B\(1/3\) = \\frac{4}{9}P_0 + \\frac{4}{9}P_1 + \\frac{1}{9}P_2$$) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### At t = 3/4 = 0.75) Tj
T*
(Coefficients for quadratic: \(1/4\)=1/16, 2\(3/4\)\(1/4\)=6/16, \(3/4\)=9/16) Tj
T*
($$B\(3/4\) = \\frac{1}{16}P_0 + \\frac{6}{16}P_1 + \\frac{9}{16}P_2$$) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 9. Applications) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- **Adobe Illustrator / Inkscape / SVG**: All paths are cubic Bzier splines) Tj
T*
(- **TrueType fonts**: Quadratic Bziers for glyph outlines) Tj
T*
(- **OpenType/PostScript fonts**: Cubic Bziers) Tj
T*
(- **CSS animations**: `cubic-bezier\(p1x, p1y, p2x, p2y\)` controls timing) Tj
T*
(- **Computer-aided design \(CAD\)**: Foundation of NURBS \(Non-Uniform Rational B-Splines\)) Tj
T*
(- **CNC machining**: Tool path generation) Tj
T*
(- **Robotics**: Smooth trajectory planning) Tj
T*
(- **Games**: Camera paths, character animations, UI transitions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
