(## 10. Relationship to Other Splines) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(| Spline Type | Based On | Properties |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Bzier | Bernstein polynomials | Global control \(moving any point affects whole curve\) |) Tj
T*
(| B-Spline | B-spline basis | Local control; pieces share knot vectors |) Tj
T*
(| NURBS | Rational B-Splines | Exact conics \(circles, ellipses\); industry standard |) Tj
T*
(| Hermite | Positions + tangents | Interpolates endpoints AND tangents |) Tj
T*
(| Catmull-Rom | 4 nearby points | Passes through all control points \(interpolating\) |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(*Sources: Wikipedia Bzier curve article; Farin, "Curves and Surfaces for CAGD" \(Morgan) Tj
T*
(Kaufmann\); Shirley, "Fundamentals of Computer Graphics"*) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# Source: de_casteljau_algorithm.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# De Casteljau's Algorithm --- Complete Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(> Wikipedia says: "De Casteljau's algorithm is a recursive method to evaluate polynomials in) Tj
T*
(Bernstein form or Bezier curves, named after its inventor Paul de Casteljau. The algorithm is) Tj
T*
(numerically stable compared to direct evaluation of polynomials. The computational complexity) Tj
T*
(is O\(dn^2\) where d is the number of dimensions and n is the number of control points.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Why Use De Casteljau?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Problem:** Direct evaluation of B\(t\) = Sum C\(n,i\)*t^i*\(1-t\)^\(n-i\)*Pi requires computing large) Tj
T*
(powers \(t^n\) and binomial coefficients, which can cause numerical overflow/precision loss for) Tj
T*
(high n.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Solution:** De Casteljau's algorithm uses only linear interpolation at each step --- a convex) Tj
T*
(combination \(weights sum to 1, both non-negative\). This guarantees numerical stability because) Tj
T*
(intermediate points always stay within the convex hull.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. The Algorithm) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Initialize \(Level 0\):) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(P_i^\(0\) = P_i    for i = 0, 1, ..., n) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Recurrence \(n rounds\):) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(P_i^\(j\) = \(1-t0\) * P_i^\(j-1\)  +  t0 * P_\(i+1\)^\(j-1\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(for j = 1, 2, ..., n and i = 0, 1, ..., n-j) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Result:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(t0\) = P_0^\(n\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The key recurrence boxed:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
