(# Source: bezier_surfaces.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(# Bezier Surfaces --- Complete Reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Definition) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A Bezier surface of degree \(m,n\) is defined by an \(m+1\)x\(n+1\) grid of control points P_{i,j}:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(           m    n) Tj
T*
(B\(u,v\) =  Sum  Sum  B_{i,m}\(u\) * B_{j,n}\(v\) * P_{i,j}) Tj
T*
(          i=0  j=0) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is a TENSOR PRODUCT surface: independently apply the 1D Bezier formula in u-direction) Tj
T*
(and v-direction.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(u in [0,1], v in [0,1]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Bicubic Bezier Patch \(Most Important\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Degree \(3,3\): 4x4 = 16 control points) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(u,v\) = Sum_{i=0}^{3} Sum_{j=0}^{3}  B_{i,3}\(u\) * B_{j,3}\(v\) * P_{i,j}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Control point grid:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(P00  P01  P02  P03) Tj
T*
(P10  P11  P12  P13) Tj
T*
(P20  P21  P22  P23) Tj
T*
(P30  P31  P32  P33) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The FOUR CORNER POINTS \(P00, P03, P30, P33\) lie ON the surface.) Tj
T*
(All other points are off-surface "handles".) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. How to Evaluate B\(u,v\) --- Two-Stage Method) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Stage 1: Fix v, evaluate each ROW as a Bezier curve in v) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For each row i=0,1,...,m:) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(Q_i\(v\) = Sum_{j=0}^{n} B_{j,n}\(v\) * P_{i,j}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(This gives m+1 new "row-reduced" control points Q_0\(v\), Q_1\(v\), ..., Q_m\(v\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Stage 2: Evaluate the result as a Bezier curve in u) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
(B\(u,v\) = Sum_{i=0}^{m} B_{i,m}\(u\) * Q_i\(v\)) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### KEY: You can do Stage 1 and Stage 2 in either order \(u then v, or v then u\)!) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
