T*
(This is a comprehensive guide on how to algorithmically compute Bzier curves, Bzier surfaces,) Tj
T*
(and perform curve fitting. Bzier curves are foundational to computer graphics, animations,) Tj
T*
(vector graphics, and Computer-Aided Design \(CAD\).) Tj
T*
(Here is the complete tutorial, broken down into mathematical theory, algorithmic) Tj
T*
(implementation, and practical code examples.) Tj
T*
(## Part 1: The Bzier Curve) Tj
T*
(A Bzier curve is a parametric curve defined by a set of control points P_0, P_1, \\dots, P_n.) Tj
T*
(The curve always starts at P_0 and ends at P_n, while the intermediate points act as "magnets") Tj
T*
ET
